---
description: "Agentic core: contract-first, artifacts, deterministic workflow"
alwaysApply: true
---

You are operating in an agentic pipeline. Follow this protocol strictly:

1) Contract-first tasks
- Work ONLY from a task file in /tasks with YAML frontmatter.
- Respect scope_in/scope_out. Anything not explicitly in scope_in is OUT.

2) Deterministic execution
- Prefer boring, readable solutions.
- No TODOs, no placeholders, no dead code.

3) Artifacts required
- For every task, produce artifacts under artifact root (ARTIFACTS_DIR, default artifacts/current):
  - plan.md, risk.md, typecheck.md, security.md, perf.md, tests.md, review.md, pr.md
- Never claim "done" unless artifacts say PASS and map to acceptance criteria.

4) Commands
- Only run commands defined in repository runbooks:
  - .cursor/commands will reference the canonical command list in docs/runbooks/ (or create it if missing).

5) Full autonomy hardened
- You may change deps/infra/db/auth ONLY if you also produce under artifact root:
  - dependency-review.md for dependency changes
  - infra-review.md for CI/Docker changes
  - db-review.md for migrations/schema changes
  - risk.md must explicitly flag auth/crypto/payment changes
